Market Segmentation: 
The Rx dermatology topical drug delivery market is segmented on the basis of product type, route of administration, category and application. The growth among segments helps you analyze niche pockets of growth and strategies to approach the market and determine your core application areas and the difference in your target markets.
On the basis of product type, the Rx dermatology topical drug delivery market is segmented into solid, liquid, semi-solid and transdermal. Solid is further segmented into powder and others. Liquid is further segmented into solution, emulsion, suspension, lotion and others. Semisolid is further segmented into creams, gel, ointments, paste, others. Transdermal is further segmented into transdermal patches and transdermal semi-solids.
On the basis of route of administration, the Rx dermatology topical drug delivery market is segmented into acne, dermatitis, psoriasis, skin infections, antiaging, skin cancer, hyperpigmentation, onychomycosis, rosacea, and others.
On the basis of category, the Rx dermatology topical drug delivery market is segmented into generic and branded.
On the basis of application, the Rx dermatology topical drug delivery market is segmented into skin infections, dermatitis, antiaging, acne, hyperpigmentation, rosacea, skin cancer, psoriasis, onychomycosis and others.
